    .subtitle We have a beautifully situated old farm house with its historic ambience, family atmosphere and a fantastic view overlooking the African savanna and a riverbed. At D端sternbrook Guest Farm you can expect a friendly and relaxed atmosphere and our individual care lets you feel at home.

.section-page
  ul.default
    li We have a large swimming pool with palm trees and a thatched lapa with a small bar and game-viewing deck also overlooking the riverbed.
    li Breakfast is served for our overnight guests on our balcony overlooking the riverbed. The breakfast is in buffet form and up to Western European standards    
    li We offer several lunch options such as salads and home-baked sandwiches. For warm meals we ask you to make a booking in advance (or the same day before 11am). (Lunch is never included in any rates)
    li Our diner is offered in family style in our lapa (summer) or our dining room (winter). Family style means we offer a fixed (not a la carte) three-course diner which varies every day. You can socialise with other guests at the table. If you want to eat at a separate table, please inform at the reception so proper arrangements can be made in advance. You can expect fish or meat (fresh from our own farm), vegetables and rice/potatoes/pasta up to European standards in the main course.   
    li We can arrange transfers from the International Airport (90km) or Windhoek (50km) to D端sternbrook Guest Farm and back.
    
